resume: Eric Wainwright , a busy impresario, is besieged by hordes of wannabe concert stars, eager for their big break. One of them is Cynthia Potter , a talented pianist, but she can't get in to see him. When she learns that Wainwright is auditioning young musicians for a children's concert tour, Cynthia dons braces and bobby sox and passes herself off as a child prodigy.
